    <tags>kobol cobol jvm compiler programming-language native graalvm</tags>
    <summary>A modern COBOL-inspired language for the JVM.</summary>
    <description>
Kobol is a modern, COBOL-inspired programming language for the JVM. It keeps the
business-logic clarity of COBOL while adding first-class types, fixed-point decimals,
pattern matching, concurrency, built-in testing, and an HTTP server — compiled to a
standalone native binary (no JVM required at runtime).

This package installs the `kobol` native compiler CLI on Windows (x64) and adds it
to your PATH via a Chocolatey shim.

After install:

    kobol --version
    kobol new my-project
    cd my-project
    kobol run
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/kobol-lang/kobol/releases/tag/v0.1.0</releaseNotes>
